along the lines of \"the backing index into which the document was written\" instead of \"associated backing index\" since a data stream may have many associated backing indices.", "url": "https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/pull/58340#discussion_r442416357", "createdAt": "2020-06-18T18:18:46Z", "author": {"login": "danhermann"}, "path": "docs/reference/docs/bulk.asciidoc", "diffHunk": "@@ -321,7 +327,8 @@ operation.\n =====\n `_index`::\n (string)\n-The index name or alias associated with the operation.\n+Name of the index associated with the operation. If the operation targeted a\n+data stream, this is the associated backing index.", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "eb111b1d1bcde8620bb0d596bbeb745b08eee18c"}, "originalPosition": 54}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ0MjQxNzk3MQ==", "bodyText": "We disallow deletes directly on a data stream because it would require searching every backing index for the specified ID. If a document is to be deleted from a data stream, the relevant backing index must be targeted directly.", "url": "https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/pull/58340#discussion_r442417971", "createdAt": "2020-06-18T18:21:41Z", "author": {"login": "danhermann"}, "path": "docs/reference/docs/delete.asciidoc", "diffHunk": "@@ -4,18 +4,19 @@\n <titleabbrev>Delete</titleabbrev>\n ++++\n \n-Removes a JSON document from the specified index.\n+Removes a JSON document from a specified data stream or index.", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "eb111b1d1bcde8620bb0d596bbeb745b08eee18c"}, "originalPosition": 5}]}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "f3648db9a860b14eefe170f55bb8e39c0c67ff9c", "author": {"user": {"login": "jrodewig", "name": "James Rodewig"}}, "url": "https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/commit/f3648db9a860b14eefe170f55bb8e39c0c67ff9c", "committedDate": "2020-06-18T19:37:45Z", "message": "fix delete API changes"}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCo